The inequality becomes \( |u - 1| + |v - 1| \le 1 \). - This equation is symmetric in all four quadrants, so we can analyze it in the first quadrant and multiply the result by 4. 2. **First Quadrant Analysis**: - In the first quadrant, \( x \ge 0 \) and \( y \ge 0 \), so \( u = x \) and \( v = y \). - The inequality simplifies to \( |x - 1| + |y - 1| \le 1 \). 3. **Case Analysis in the First Quadrant**: - **Case 1**: \( x \ge 1 \) and \( y \ge 1 \) - The inequality becomes \( x + y \le 3 \). This forms a triangle with vertices at \( (1, 1) \), \( (1, 2) \), and \( (2, 1) \). The area is \( 0.5 \). - **Case 2**: \( x \ge 1 \) and \( y < 1 \) - The inequality becomes \( x - y \le 1 \). This forms a triangle with vertices at \( (1, 0) \), \( (1, 1) \), and \( (2, 1) \). The area is \( 0.5 \). - **Case 3**: \( x < 1 \) and \( y \ge 1 \) - The inequality becomes \( y - x \le 1 \). This forms a triangle with vertices at \( (0, 1) \), \( (1, 1) \), and \( (1, 2) \). The area is \( 0.5 \). - **Case 4**: \( x < 1 \) and \( y < 1 \) - The inequality becomes \( x + y \ge 1 \). This forms a triangle with vertices at \( (1, 0) \), \( (0, 1) \), and \( (1, 1) \). The area is \( 0.5 \). 4. **Total Area in the First Quadrant**: - Summing the areas of all four cases in the first quadrant gives \( 0.5 + 0.5 + 0.5 + 0.5 = 2 \). 5. **Extending to All Quadrants**: - Since the problem is symmetric in all four quadrants, we multiply the area found in the first quadrant by 4: - Total area \( = 4 \times 2 = 8 \). Thus, the area of the region defined by the inequality \( ||x| - 1| + ||y| - 1| \le 1 \) is \(\boxed{8}\).
